1
00:01:21,540 --> 00:01:25,710
(Vehicle Approaching)

2
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:56,740
(Indistinct Chattering)

3
00:02:30,980 --> 00:02:33,230
Une bière, s'il vous plaît.

4
00:02:52,790 --> 00:02:54,550
Merci.

5
00:04:35,230 --> 00:04:37,060
(Door Opens)

6
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:40,480
(French) We are closed.

7
00:04:40,610 --> 00:04:42,320
Just a small drink.

8
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,080
The toilets?

9
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,830
(Telephone)

10
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:39,040
(Door Opens)

11
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:47,760
(French)
A quick drink and then I'll leave.

12
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,680
(Irish Accent)
Why are you rushing off?

13
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:55,980
- Hmm?
- I said, why are you rushing off?

14
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,770
(French) I don't understand.

15
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,020
The man from Bristol called ya.

16
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:09,410
- What man?
- The man in the wheelchair.

17
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:11,950
(Car Horn)

18
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:18,580
(Vehicle Pulls Up)

19
00:06:46,110 --> 00:06:48,490
What were you doing back here?

20
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:51,490
Lady,...

21
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:55,160
... I never walk into a place
I don't know how to walk out of.

22
00:06:56,410 --> 00:06:58,290
Then why would you get into that van?

23
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:00,790
You know the reason.

24
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:14,030
Make yourselves at home.

25
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,660
You've come a long way.

26
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:19,750
- Thanks for coming.
- What's the job?

27
00:08:19,910 --> 00:08:23,620
There's some people
who have something we require.

28
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:27,170
- And we want you to get it from them.
- It involves shooting?

29
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:30,880
You must be tired.

30
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,180
We'll tell you more tomorrow.

31
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:43,980
Seven fat years
and seven lean years.

32
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:46,900
- That's what it says in the Bible.
- You ever kill anybody?

33
00:08:47,020 --> 00:08:49,570
I hurt somebody's feelings once.

34
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,870
Don't I know you?

35
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:03,410
I don't think so. I'd remember.

36
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,420
Okay, two-hour shifts.

37
00:09:12,590 --> 00:09:15,260
I'll watch the front,
you guys watch the back.

38
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:19,100
Merci.

39
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:25,980
(Truck Horn)

40
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:33,820
You awake, then?

41
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:38,240
Hmm?

42
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,620
How we doing?

43
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:48,830
Yep.

44
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,980
You labour or management?

45
00:10:09,230 --> 00:10:13,230
If I was management,
I wouldn't have given you a cigarette.

46
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:18,990
I am the tour guide.
Over there is the Eiffel Tower.

47
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:21,830
Over here, the Louvre.
Over there, les toilettes.

48
00:10:21,990 --> 00:10:24,290
What do I call you?

49
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:27,120
- My name is Vincent.
- Sam.

50
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:35,050
As per the agreement,
your salary will be $5,000 a week...

51
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:37,840
...with a minimum
of four weeks work.

52
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:40,340
On the successful completion
of the mission,...

53
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:44,310
...you will each receive
a bonus of $20,000.

54
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:49,850
And by the way,
my name is Deirdre.

55
00:10:49,980 --> 00:10:52,900
- The broad outlines of the mission are...
- Who are your principals?

56
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:54,860
For you,
there's no one but myself.

57
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:56,990
Huh?

58
00:10:57,110 --> 00:11:00,070
And what can we infer
from your charming Irish lilt?

59
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:03,280
- Anything you like.
- Where's the equipment?

60
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:05,950
Tell me what you need, make a list,
and give it to Vincent.

61
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:09,290
- Some of the equipment's quite technical.
- If it's in Paris, I'll find it.

62
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:12,880
This is what we're after.

63
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:16,960
We need to take it intact from several
men who'll be intent on preventing us.

64
00:11:17,130 --> 00:11:19,340
- How many men?
- You American?

65
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:23,300
I think the group will be between
five and eight. No more than eight.

66
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:27,980
- You don't know for sure?
- Not now but I will know before the event.

67
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:31,600
If you don't know,
why say between five and eight?

68
00:11:31,730 --> 00:11:33,610
There's two to three cars.
The group's traveling.

69
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:35,070
- They're not in Paris?
- No.

70
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:36,070
Where are they?

71
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:38,780
- You'll find out soon enough.
- What's in the case?

72
00:11:40,530 --> 00:11:43,450
Our plan, in broad strokes, is an ambush.

73
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:46,120
It's to hit the car,
to take them in transit.

74
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:50,000
- Transit? City? Country?
- Right now, as I said, I don't know.

75
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,500
But we've to move very quickly.

76
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:57,050
We'll start with this: Ambush
and assault on two to three vehicles,...

77
00:11:57,170 --> 00:12:01,840
...five to eight men, and our objective
is the safe retrieval of this case.

78
00:12:01,970 --> 00:12:05,640
Tell Vincent
what it is you'll need.

79
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:10,600
What do we know about them?
Are they French? Who are they?

80
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:14,020
All you need to know right now
is that they're very unpleasant.

81
00:12:14,190 --> 00:12:18,730
- You've done this kind of thing before?
- You know...

82
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:19,940
How difficult can it be?

83
00:12:20,070 --> 00:12:22,150
We have no idea
how these men will be armed?

84
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:24,700
It seems they'll be
very well armed, indeed.

85
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:26,870
Where are we going and
how are we getting back from there?

86
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:30,120
It'll be in France, and the group
will disband at the RV point.

87
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:33,870
- (French) What does she mean?
- After that, we're on our own.

88
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,670
- It's a military term.
- That's right.

89
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:38,340
Larry, tell Vincent what you'll need.

90
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:43,340
Something very fast. Audi S-8.
Something that can shove.

91
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:46,180
I'm going to have it for you
by the afternoon.

92
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:49,970
I'll also need a nitrous system.
I've got the specs.

93
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:57,060
What do you use, weapons-wise?

94
00:12:57,230 --> 00:12:59,400
- Hmm?
- Weapons.

95
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:02,570
- I'm a... I'm a weapons man.
- Weapons man.

96
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:04,570
- Yeah.
- Okay.

97
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:08,700
They tend to settle the argument.
So what do you favor?

98
00:13:08,870 --> 00:13:12,410
Well, you know. It's a toolbox.
You put the tools in for the job.

99
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:13,710
What?

100
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:16,920
You know,
I actually favor the old 191 1 .

101
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:20,420
.45. Old gun.

102
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:24,380
It served my country well.
A long time.

103
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:26,890
Your country!

104
00:13:27,050 --> 00:13:29,050
Not done too well, have you,
last few wars?

105
00:13:29,220 --> 00:13:31,600
Perhaps not, but at least
we don't go around whining about it.

106
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:35,020
You ex-military?

107
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:37,100
No, I got my job
through the New York Times.

108
00:13:38,730 --> 00:13:41,980
- (French) Don't let him get you down.
- It don't mean nothing to me.

109
00:13:42,110 --> 00:13:43,900
I say what I think.

110
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:46,450
Are you ex-military?

111
00:13:46,610 --> 00:13:48,780
Boys at Hereford?

112
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:51,620
I'm sorry, but I'd like to go backwards.
The line of retreat is...

113
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:56,210
She just told you.
We meet back at the RV, disband.

114
00:13:56,370 --> 00:14:00,290
I understand. I'm just trying to get
a vague notion of the opposition.

115
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:06,090
We're gonna cause some animosity.
How many will be coming after us?

116
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:09,260
- You worried about your own skin?
- Yeah, I am.

117
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:11,260
It covers my body.

118
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:16,060
All your concerns will be addressed
before we leave.

119
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,690
- Electronics and commo.
- Not more than three cars?

120
00:14:18,810 --> 00:14:20,190
That is our information.

121
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:23,030
- Can you get me a simulator?
- What's a simulator?

122
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:26,360
Gunpowder. Sound only, no lead.
Sounds like a pistol.

123
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:28,030
Quite diverting.

124
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:31,780
Listen, I'm also gonna need
some bigger injection jets.

125
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:34,580
The Bosch is not gonna do it.
They have to be custom-made.

126
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:37,620
We going north? We going south?

127
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,960
I'd like some new clothes.

128
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,750
- Vincent will sort you out.
- I'll take care of it.

129
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:53,760
- So what brought you here?
- A fella that doesn't work so well.

130
00:14:55,140 --> 00:14:57,480
The man in the wheelchair?

131
00:14:58,390 --> 00:14:59,850
How did he get there?

132
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:04,780
That was in your neck of the woods,
back in the late unpleasantness.

133
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,450
Good reflexes.

134
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,750
Oh, yeah.

135
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:23,460
They die hard.

136
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:34,010
- Interrogation.
- What?

137
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:38,180
- Methods to withstand interrogation.
- You've done that?

138
00:15:38,350 --> 00:15:41,270
We were taught
to hold out indefinitely.

139
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:46,820
- Nobody can hold out indefinitely.
- Ah, is that so?

140
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:52,530
Everybody has a limit. I spent
some time in interrogation... once.

141
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:54,990
- They make it hard on you?
- They don't make it easy.

142
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:59,410
Yeah, it was unpleasant.
I held out as long as I could.

143
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:02,210
All the stuff they tried.

144
00:16:02,330 --> 00:16:04,630
You just can't hold out for ever.

145
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:07,420
- Impossible.
- How'd they finally get to you?

146
00:16:07,590 --> 00:16:10,300
- They gave me a grasshopper.
- What's a grasshopper?

147
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:14,930
That's two part gin, two part brandy,
one part crème de menthe...

148
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,100
Fucking smartass!

149
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:20,980
- Can you find this place?
- Of course.

150
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:23,020
I know it.

151
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:26,150
That's where
they wanna do the exchange.

152
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,110
You're gonna exchange for cash?

153
00:16:29,150 --> 00:16:33,240
- You know these people?
- My people know them.

154
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:35,620
Your people have done business
with them before?

155
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:38,540
Or these people
just gave your people a number?

156
00:16:49,340 --> 00:16:51,590
Larry.

157
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:58,930
Okay. If we're gonna do it,
let's do the goddamn thing right.

158
00:17:01,850 --> 00:17:04,600
- Hey!
- I'm busy.

159
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:08,190
Okay, come on. Let's go.

160
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:11,820
The answers to your questions
I'll know when I get back.

161
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:15,030
- I'll go with you.
- Go with them.

162
00:17:35,340 --> 00:17:37,180
Who does this girl work for?

163
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:41,640
Well, she works for our betters.

164
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:44,940
It seems that's what
we're meant to know.

165
00:17:52,730 --> 00:17:55,700
Always a waiting game.

166
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:59,620
- What?
- It's a waiting game.

167
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:05,410
Hey, wait.
Would you not do that, please?

168
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:10,590
Bad for the night vision, yeah?

169
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,050
There they are.

170
00:19:07,390 --> 00:19:10,060
- You have the list?
- Yes, I have it.

171
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:11,900
Give it to me.

172
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:17,740
Money?

173
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:21,530
Okay. You follow my lead.

174
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:23,910
Just make sure you watch my back.

175
00:19:28,710 --> 00:19:30,370
(French) Don't make any sudden moves.

176
00:19:30,870 --> 00:19:34,420
Just because we're buying guns
doesn't mean we didn't bring any.

177
00:19:34,550 --> 00:19:37,800
Don't worry. Everything's fine.

178
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:43,050
You want to back him up?

179
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:49,140
What would I profit from your death?

180
00:19:49,270 --> 00:19:52,690
- Well, you'd have the money.
- I have the money already.

181
00:19:54,650 --> 00:19:57,070
I'll watch the back.

182
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,780
- (French) Have you got it all?
- Oui.

183
00:20:04,660 --> 00:20:08,000
- You're sure?
- Of course. Come and see.

184
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:19,300
There it is!

185
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:41,740
It's not all here.

186
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,910
- Vincent.
- What?

187
00:20:49,910 --> 00:20:52,580
It's not all here.

188
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:54,500
- C'est tout?
- Ah, non, non, non.

189
00:20:54,710 --> 00:20:58,920
Le patron va contrôler I'argent.
Vous aurez le reste de la marchandise.

190
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:03,050
Tiens. Il est lå dans la voiture,
avec le patron.

191
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:07,600
He said the rest is in the other car.
The boss wants to check the money.

192
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:10,890
(French)
If he agrees, we have no problem.

193
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:12,810
Here, take the car keys.

194
00:21:12,940 --> 00:21:15,980
Go on. Take them.

195
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:21,650
Come on. Come.

196
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,990
Okay, give me...
Give me some of the money.

197
00:21:33,210 --> 00:21:36,170
Give me some of the money!

198
00:21:38,170 --> 00:21:40,420
- Okay.
- You aren't going in there?

199
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:44,680
- Yeah, I am, and so are you.
- Why am I going in there?

200
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:48,800
- Why? To protect me.
- There is no protection there.

201
00:21:48,930 --> 00:21:52,390
If it's a come-on, we're fish in a barrel.
Why do they want you in there?

202
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:54,890
- What are you, crazy?
- You know, you think too hard.

203
00:21:55,060 --> 00:21:58,650
Nobody ever told me that before.
But I wouldn't go in there.

204
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:03,860
- What is it, Sam?
- I don't like it. Look at it.

205
00:22:05,570 --> 00:22:07,410
Okay, okay.

206
00:22:07,570 --> 00:22:09,950
Okay, let's just do it.
Let's just do it and be done, yeah?

207
00:22:10,950 --> 00:22:12,330
You don't wanna go in there.

208
00:22:13,910 --> 00:22:17,830
- I'm getting paid to go. It's that simple.
- Okay, come on. Let's go.

209
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:21,550
If anything goes down,
get next to one of those guys.

210
00:22:21,670 --> 00:22:23,800
If there's a sniper,
he'll be afraid to shoot his own guy.

211
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,590
- Let's go!
- All right.

212
00:22:47,780 --> 00:22:49,660
Stop!

213
00:22:49,780 --> 00:22:51,950
(French) Stay where you are.

214
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:10,430
So, everything's fine.

215
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:17,060
(Boat Horn)

216
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,400
Shit! I can't see! I can't see!

217
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:38,330
Have some of this!

218
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,550
Fucking arse-hole!

219
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:52,300
- Fucking have some more, you bastards!
- (Siren)

220
00:23:54,050 --> 00:23:55,930
Come on! Come on!

221
00:23:57,390 --> 00:23:59,770
- (Gunfire Continues)
- Let's go!

222
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:04,150
- No! You goddamn...
- Come on! Let's go!

223
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,120
- Is anybody hurt?
- We're fine.

224
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:25,880
Almost a bit of raspberry jam
back there, yeah?

225
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,880
A bit of raspberry jam back there!

226
00:24:28,010 --> 00:24:30,050
(Tyres Screeching)

227
00:24:31,630 --> 00:24:35,300
Got the swag, kept the money.
Job well done.

228
00:24:35,430 --> 00:24:37,310
That's a fact. That is a fact.

229
00:24:37,470 --> 00:24:39,220
(Siren)

230
00:25:02,830 --> 00:25:03,920
Slow down. Slow down.

231
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:08,170
I think I have to stop.

232
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:37,950
Thank you.

233
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:41,450
(Spence Coughing)

234
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:51,420
Why did you take this job?

235
00:25:54,010 --> 00:25:56,010
My friend, I need the money.

236
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:59,510
(French) The money is here.

237
00:26:03,850 --> 00:26:06,980
That's what this is, you know? Money.

238
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:12,990
Yeah, but who are our employers?

239
00:26:15,650 --> 00:26:17,490
You're right.

240
00:26:20,990 --> 00:26:23,910
(Tannoy announcement in French)

241
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:47,850
Excuse me.

242
00:26:48,020 --> 00:26:50,520
Excuse me, monsieur.

243
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:01,700
(Irish Accent)
The Russians are bidding for the case.

244
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:05,830
The case is in Nice.
They're trying to sell it to the Russians.

245
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:09,210
They're staying at
the Villa Belle Mer in Nice.

246
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:14,840
- The team isn't ready.
