01:23:29,250 --> 01:23:32,970
The ronin could have hired
themselves to new masters.

747
01:23:33,090 --> 01:23:35,220
They could have fought
for themselves.

748
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:38,350
But they chose honor.
They chose myth.

749
01:23:39,560 --> 01:23:41,350
They chose wrong.

750
01:23:49,190 --> 01:23:51,690
Seppu... Seppu... what?

751
01:23:51,860 --> 01:23:54,030
Yes, seppuku.

752
01:23:54,150 --> 01:23:56,370
Disembowelment.

753
01:23:56,530 --> 01:23:59,240
The sword goes in here.

754
01:23:59,370 --> 01:24:01,620
(Slicing Sound)

755
01:24:09,380 --> 01:24:11,380
[Sam] Are you sure
this address is good?

756
01:24:11,550 --> 01:24:13,420
[Vincent] Jean-Pierre gave it to me.

757
01:24:46,920 --> 01:24:50,380
Under the bridge by the river...

758
01:24:50,500 --> 01:24:53,170
How did you know
it was an ambush?

759
01:24:53,300 --> 01:24:55,720
Whenever there is any doubt,
there is no doubt.

760
01:24:55,880 --> 01:24:57,720
That's the first thing
they teach you.

761
01:25:01,510 --> 01:25:04,180
Who taught you?

762
01:25:04,350 --> 01:25:07,480
I don't remember.
That's the second thing they teach you.

763
01:25:12,690 --> 01:25:14,940
All good things
come to those who wait.

764
01:25:45,770 --> 01:25:49,350
- Why is Gregor still alive?
- He's taking them to the package.

765
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:15,130
How ya doing?

766
01:26:23,010 --> 01:26:25,720
What are you...
What are you gonna do to me?

767
01:26:25,890 --> 01:26:31,100
Let's just be calm for one more moment.
One more moment.

768
01:26:43,820 --> 01:26:45,870
Why? Why?

769
01:26:45,990 --> 01:26:48,040
You know why.

770
01:26:48,160 --> 01:26:50,290
No. You don't wanna do that.

771
01:26:54,130 --> 01:26:55,090
You can't.

772
01:27:00,050 --> 01:27:00,670
Get back!

773
01:27:02,300 --> 01:27:04,260
Get in the fucking car!

774
01:27:14,230 --> 01:27:15,770
Why didn't you shoot her?

775
01:28:07,990 --> 01:28:09,700
Take the tunnel, now!

776
01:28:09,830 --> 01:28:11,790
[Deirdre] Oh, Christ!

777
01:28:14,120 --> 01:28:16,210
Eh, merde!

778
01:28:47,870 --> 01:28:49,830
(Siren)

779
01:29:33,120 --> 01:29:35,620
(Horns Honking)

780
01:30:11,110 --> 01:30:13,120
(Tyres Screeching)

781
01:31:10,550 --> 01:31:14,050
(Horns Honking)

782
01:31:24,730 --> 01:31:26,060
Come on! Come on!

783
01:31:51,220 --> 01:31:53,130
All right, you fuck!

784
01:33:46,710 --> 01:33:48,710
(Deirdre Screaming)

785
01:34:00,590 --> 01:34:03,430
(Coughing)

786
01:34:14,480 --> 01:34:16,990
(Gunfire)

787
01:34:21,530 --> 01:34:23,740
(Shouting In French)

788
01:34:34,920 --> 01:34:37,170
(Groaning)

789
01:35:20,170 --> 01:35:22,510
[Vincent] Where could he be?

790
01:35:22,630 --> 01:35:26,560
- Where could he be?
- Hmm.

791
01:35:26,720 --> 01:35:30,140
The Irish and the Russians are looking
for him. So where does he go?

792
01:35:30,270 --> 01:35:34,100
He goes to the Russians
to make the deal for the case.

793
01:35:34,230 --> 01:35:37,690
Gregor ain't coming in unless
he can figure out a safe exchange.

794
01:35:37,860 --> 01:35:39,990
He knows they'll kill him for the case
rather than pay him for it.

795
01:35:40,110 --> 01:35:45,450
He's got to work it out soon
before the Irish find him.

796
01:35:46,830 --> 01:35:48,620
So where does he go?

797
01:35:50,500 --> 01:35:52,330
You go to what you know.

798
01:35:55,920 --> 01:35:59,710
He's KGB.
He goes to one of his old safe houses.

799
01:36:01,220 --> 01:36:03,800
No, they're all blown.

800
01:36:03,970 --> 01:36:06,300
Where does he go?

801
01:36:06,470 --> 01:36:08,470
(Sighs)

802
01:36:12,100 --> 01:36:15,480
So, you're on the run.
Where do you go?

803
01:36:15,650 --> 01:36:17,520
Hmm?

804
01:36:21,690 --> 01:36:26,070
Where's he been? Where's he been?
Where's he been? Where's he been?

805
01:36:26,240 --> 01:36:28,830
(Chattering In French)

806
01:36:37,880 --> 01:36:40,420
He made the fake case.

807
01:36:40,550 --> 01:36:42,880
He had the fake case made.

808
01:36:43,050 --> 01:36:46,470
Gregor. He had it made.

809
01:36:46,590 --> 01:36:49,140
He had to have had it made.

810
01:36:50,680 --> 01:36:53,770
In Paris, before we went to Nice.

811
01:36:53,890 --> 01:36:55,690
He didn't have time to have it made.

812
01:36:55,810 --> 01:36:57,980
He bought something that looked like it,
then spray-painted it.

813
01:36:58,110 --> 01:37:00,650
Where did he get the spray?
He never left the room.

814
01:37:00,770 --> 01:37:02,730
Where did he get the case?

815
01:37:12,410 --> 01:37:14,620
[Vincent] Excusez-moi, monsieur.

816
01:37:35,980 --> 01:37:37,770
It's a case for ice skates.

817
01:37:41,400 --> 01:37:43,280
Why ice skates?

818
01:37:45,610 --> 01:37:47,570
And why would Gregor
know an ice-skate case?

819
01:37:49,620 --> 01:37:52,080
He didn't have time to have it made.

820
01:37:52,240 --> 01:37:57,000
He didn't have time to have it made.
The Russians made it.

821
01:37:59,000 --> 01:38:01,540
The Russians made it.

822
01:38:04,710 --> 01:38:06,550
We're following the wrong people.

823
01:38:06,720 --> 01:38:09,590
We don't have to find Gregor.

824
01:38:09,760 --> 01:38:12,430
We find the Russians,
they will take us to him.

825
01:38:12,600 --> 01:38:16,430
(Russian) You've lived in Paris
a long time. You know the people.

826
01:38:16,560 --> 01:38:19,560
- I get around.
- You meet the new Russians.

827
01:38:19,690 --> 01:38:23,570
You know how it is.
Ex-spies. Now it's Mafia.

828
01:38:24,480 --> 01:38:26,570
Under diplomatic cover.

829
01:38:28,150 --> 01:38:29,110
KGB?

830
01:38:29,400 --> 01:38:30,360
Ex-KGB.

831
01:38:30,820 --> 01:38:35,370
(French) Heavy hitters, gamblers,
lots of money, big cars.

832
01:38:35,490 --> 01:38:36,870
(Russian) They live like Tsars.
Throw money away.

833
01:38:37,000 --> 01:38:38,830
Fur hats are expensive.

834
01:38:38,960 --> 01:38:44,340
- And bodyguards.
- Expensive coats, Dr Zhivago.

835
01:38:44,460 --> 01:38:47,590
I have a lot of work, no time.

836
01:38:49,130 --> 01:38:50,720
I understand.

837
01:38:52,510 --> 01:38:54,180
All right. Let's go.

838
01:38:55,140 --> 01:38:56,100
Okay.

839
01:39:03,310 --> 01:39:04,860
(French) It will be fine.

840
01:39:06,400 --> 01:39:08,240
The guy is gonna reach out.

841
01:39:08,360 --> 01:39:10,240
Is he any good?

842
01:39:10,400 --> 01:39:13,240
Jean-Pierre says if it's Russian
and it's in Paris...

843
01:39:13,370 --> 01:39:15,370
(Speaking Russian)

844
01:39:24,380 --> 01:39:27,750
(French) If I wanted to find Russians
in Paris this week,...

845
01:39:27,880 --> 01:39:32,010
...I'd go to the ice show.

846
01:39:40,930 --> 01:39:44,350
(Crowd Chattering)

847
01:39:44,520 --> 01:39:47,360
(Applause, Cheering)

848
01:40:46,080 --> 01:40:48,170
- Bonsoir, Pierre.
- Bonsoir.

849
01:40:48,290 --> 01:40:50,170
Je vais payer pour votre soeur.

850
01:40:50,300 --> 01:40:53,630
Oh, merci beaucoup,
Mademoiselle Kirilova.

851
01:41:00,180 --> 01:41:04,890
(French)
I'll trade you a cigarette for a favor.

852
01:41:05,480 --> 01:41:07,350
The favor is, steer clear of those guys.

853
01:41:07,480 --> 01:41:08,940
Who? The Russians?

854
01:41:15,490 --> 01:41:17,660
They sure throw their money around.

855
01:41:18,820 --> 01:41:19,870
Bonsoir.

856
01:41:19,990 --> 01:41:22,160
- Ca va?
- Salut.

857
01:41:25,500 --> 01:41:27,330
- Bonsoir.
- Ah, bonsoir.

858
01:41:33,920 --> 01:41:38,220
The Russian is seeing Natacha Kirilova,
the star of the ice show.

859
01:41:38,340 --> 01:41:41,890
He spends every evening in the audience.

860
01:41:43,180 --> 01:41:44,640
How did you find that out?

861
01:41:44,770 --> 01:41:48,020
We went to high school together.

862
01:41:48,150 --> 01:41:49,100
(Clapping)

863
01:42:22,300 --> 01:42:24,720
(Russian) Mikhi, is everything all right?

864
01:42:25,560 --> 01:42:26,930
Everything is fine.

865
01:42:28,190 --> 01:42:29,190
Sweet girl.

866
01:42:32,020 --> 01:42:32,980
Go. Go on.

867
01:42:38,200 --> 01:42:40,990
(Applause, Cheering)

868
01:42:52,000 --> 01:42:53,710
(PA System In French)
Ladies and gentlemen!

869
01:42:53,840 --> 01:42:57,090
We are very proud to present...

870
01:42:57,210 --> 01:43:04,050
...two-time Olympic champion
and three-time World champion,...

871
01:43:04,180 --> 01:43:07,770
...Natacha Kirilova!

872
01:43:17,110 --> 01:43:23,530
(Applause Fades)

873
01:44:18,380 --> 01:44:21,340
(Applause, Whistling)

874
01:44:40,610 --> 01:44:43,450
(Applause)

875
01:45:14,100 --> 01:45:15,980
Let's go.

876
01:45:29,370 --> 01:45:31,450
(Russian) Wait out here.

877
01:45:36,460 --> 01:45:38,670
Yes, he is.

878
01:45:38,790 --> 01:45:40,840
Hello, Mikhi.

879
01:45:41,000 --> 01:45:44,970
- The meeting is not till later tonight.
- The meeting's now.

880
01:45:45,170 --> 01:45:48,220
(Crowd Applauding)

881
01:45:48,390 --> 01:45:49,930
You have the money?

882
01:45:51,310 --> 01:45:55,180
Well, we were going to go back
to get it before the meet.

883
01:45:55,310 --> 01:45:56,390
I don't think so.

884
01:45:57,900 --> 01:45:59,770
You have the money?

885
01:46:04,230 --> 01:46:07,200
I might have the money.
Where is the case?

886
01:46:07,320 --> 01:46:11,660
No, you have to do it.
I couldn't live with myself.

887
01:46:24,670 --> 01:46:26,510
I have the money.

888
01:46:26,670 --> 01:46:29,130
We conclude this now
and part friends.

889
01:46:29,260 --> 01:46:31,010
Okay?

890
01:46:33,930 --> 01:46:34,970
Where is the case?

891
01:46:47,400 --> 01:46:49,240
I'd like to be paid now.

892
01:46:54,870 --> 01:46:57,000
No doubt.

893
01:47:01,790 --> 01:47:03,630
Now tell me the other part.

894
01:47:05,130 --> 01:47:07,260
The other part?

895
01:47:07,420 --> 01:47:09,260
I'm leaving.

896
01:47:09,420 --> 01:47:12,260
I'm taking my fee and I'm leaving.

897
01:47:13,930 --> 01:47:16,970
I have a person with a rifle in the stadium.

898
01:47:17,220 --> 01:47:20,020
I've worked with her for years.
She never misses.

899
01:47:20,190 --> 01:47:23,110
I will call.

900
01:47:23,270 --> 01:47:25,570
I have to call within 45 seconds...

901
01:47:25,730 --> 01:47:27,780
...to say that I'm leaving,...

902
01:47:27,940 --> 01:47:31,070
...and then in another 10 minutes
to say that I'm safe.

903
01:47:32,780 --> 01:47:36,660
Should I be unable to call,
your friend will be shot.

904
01:47:46,550 --> 01:47:48,380
30 seconds, Mikhi.

905
01:47:49,840 --> 01:47:52,300
- (French) We need to get inside.
- You can't pass without badges.

906
01:47:59,680 --> 01:48:01,480
20 seconds.

907
01:48:12,200 --> 01:48:13,160
10 seconds.

908
01:48:28,800 --> 01:48:29,340
(Gunshot)

909
01:48:42,430 --> 01:48:45,270
(French) There were two of them.

910
01:48:45,400 --> 01:48:47,060
They were looking for those guys.

911
01:48:47,190 --> 01:48:49,320
Just a minute, sir!

912
01:48:49,480 --> 01:48:51,360
(Camera Shutters Clicking)

913
01:49:05,920 --> 01:49:09,800
(French) I am a Chilean citizen,
as you can see from my passport.

914
01:49:09,920 --> 01:49:11,550
Merci.

915
01:49:14,010 --> 01:49:16,340
(Chattering, Shouting)

916
01:49:50,040 --> 01:49:53,170
- Mama!
- Shh, shh, shh.

917
01:49:59,050 --> 01:50:00,640
Katchev!

918
01:50:00,760 --> 01:50:01,890
Qu'est-ce qui se passe?

919
01:50:04,640 --> 01:50:07,310
(Screaming)

920
01:50:16,950 --> 01:50:17,910
Stay with him.

921
01:50:50,810 --> 01:50:53,320
Get out of here.
Get out of here!

922
01:50:53,480 --> 01:50:56,280
Get out of the car.
Walk away. Walk away!

923
01:50:56,400 --> 01:50:59,200
Walk away! Go. Go.

924
01:50:59,320 --> 01:51:02,160
- I will if you will.
- Just go.

925
01:51:02,280 --> 01:51:04,700
Come with me.
Forget about the case.

926
01:51:09,160 --> 01:51:11,630
I didn't come for the case.
I came for your boss.

927
01:51:13,500 --> 01:51:16,050
I came for Seamus. I came for him.

928
01:51:17,460 --> 01:51:22,340
Just get out of here.
I never left. Don't you see?

929
01:51:23,760 --> 01:51:26,060
Get out of the way!
Get out of the way!

930
01:51:29,430 --> 01:51:31,060
(Sirens)

931
01:51:34,440 --> 01:51:35,730
Get out of the way!

932
01:51:35,860 --> 01:51:37,150
(French) This way is blocked.

933
01:52:05,010 --> 01:52:06,850
I can take you in or leave you here.

934
01:52:08,390 --> 01:52:09,600
There. That's him with the case.

935
01:52:09,730 --> 01:52:11,810
(French) Sir! Over here, please.

936
01:52:11,940 --> 01:52:12,640
Wait! Wait!

937
01:52:13,770 --> 01:52:15,480
(Screaming, Shouting)

938
01:52:20,320 --> 01:52:23,320
(French) There are more back there!

939
01:52:54,730 --> 01:52:57,150
(Panting)

940
01:53:00,650 --> 01:53:02,490
[Seamus] Stay where you are!
Stay where you are!

941
01:53:02,610 --> 01:53:06,450
Don't move! Shut your fucking mouth up!
Shut your mouth!

942
01:53:13,290 --> 01:53:17,330
(Gasping, Sobbing)

943
01:53:20,500 --> 01:53:22,300
You stupid shite.

944
01:53:22,510 --> 01:53:26,010
- You're a dead man.
- (Gunfire)

945
01:53:48,570 --> 01:53:50,910
(Radio)
This is the BBC World Service.

946
01:53:51,080 --> 01:53:53,750
It was announced today,
after almost 30 years...

947
01:53:53,870 --> 01:53:57,210
...of bloody and seemingly intractable
civil conflict in Northern Ireland,...

948
01:53:57,330 --> 01:53:59,210
...that a peace agreement
has been reached between...

949
01:53:59,380 --> 01:54:02,550
...the predominantly Protestant
government of that British-ruled enclave,...

950
01:54:02,710 --> 01:54:05,220
- ...and the Irish resistance...
- (Overlapping Radio Reports)

951
01:54:10,050 --> 01:54:13,600
...have told CNN that it was
the apprehension and slaying...

952
01:54:13,770 --> 01:54:18,560
...in France of the Irish terrorist Seamus
O'Rourke, by parties still unknown,...

953
01:54:18,690 --> 01:54:20,980
...that contributed a stability,
largely allowing...

954
01:54:21,110 --> 01:54:25,070
...the negotiations to proceed
to their historic conclusion today.

955
01:54:25,240 --> 01:54:28,110
O'Rourke had earlier
been denounced by the IRA,...

956
01:54:28,280 --> 01:54:32,330
...the military wing of Sinn Fein,
as a rogue breakaway operative.

957
01:54:34,870 --> 01:54:38,170
Well, then, good knowing ya.

958
01:54:48,930 --> 01:54:49,890
Hmm?

959
01:54:50,010 --> 01:54:53,180
- I'm sorry?
- You said something.

960
01:54:53,310 --> 01:54:56,770
I said she would not
be coming back here.

961
01:54:58,980 --> 01:55:03,400
Yeah. She would
not be coming back here, would she?

962
01:55:09,700 --> 01:55:11,740
I can't even put my hand in my pocket
to pay the bill.

963
01:55:11,870 --> 01:55:13,990
I'll get it.

964
01:55:16,540 --> 01:55:18,330
I'll get the next one.

965
01:55:24,710 --> 01:55:26,420
What was in the case?

966
01:55:26,670 --> 01:55:28,670
I don't remember.

967
01:55:30,050 --> 01:55:31,550
Lesson number two.

968
01:55:33,760 --> 01:55:35,600
Keep in touch.

969
01:55:54,160 --> 01:55:55,950
Let's go.

970
01:56:09,210 --> 01:56:11,970
[Vincent]
No questions, no answers.

971
01:56:12,090 --> 01:56:14,180
That's the business we're in.

972
01:56:14,300 --> 01:56:16,560
You accept it and move on.

973
01:56:18,020 --> 01:56:20,770
Maybe that's lesson number three.